Optimizing Multimodal Deep Learning Architectures for Early Disease Detection
1. Overview
This document provides detailed documentation for the three benchmark datasets used in the multimodal deep learning framework for early disease detection. Each dataset contributes a distinct data modality — medical imaging, structured electronic health records (EHR), and sequential physiological time-series — enabling the model to learn complementary clinical representations across modalities.

