5. Quick Start — Synthetic Data
If you wish to run and test the code immediately without downloading and registering for the real datasets, a synthetic data generator is provided. It generates realistic synthetic versions of all three datasets that mimic the statistical properties of the originals.
Run the generator:
python data/generate_synthetic_data.py
This will generate 200 synthetic X-ray images, 200 EHR records, and 200 ECG signals in the data/synthetic/ directory. You can then train the model using:
python src/train.py --config configs/train_config.yaml
